metacolsdetails.Reproducibility: The proportion of technical replicate assay pairs for which the marker score is consistent
metacolsdetails.Qpmr: The average of the normalized non-zero tag read counts divided by the standard deviation of the normalized non-zero tag read counts (If standard deviation is zero or near zero, the Qpmr value will be 100).
metacolsdetails.CallRate: The proportion of samples for which the genotype call is either "1" or "0", rather than "-"
metacolsdetails.OneRatio: The proportion of samples for which the genotype score is "1"
metacolsdetails.AvgReadDepth: The sum of the tag read counts for all samples, divided by the number of samples with non-zero tag read counts.
metacolsdetails.AlleleSequence: The sequence of the tag which is present in samples with genotype score "1"
metacolsdetails.TrimmedSequence: Same as the full sequence, but with removed adapters in short marker tags
metacolsdetails.CloneID: Unique identifier of the sequence tag
metacolsdetails.StDevReadDepth: The standard deviation of the number of tag reads for all samples with non-zero tag read counts

alncoldetails.Chrom_: Contig(s) with the best alignment of marker / tag to an existing model genome
alncoldetails.AlnEvalue_: E value of the best alignment to an existing model genome
alncoldetails.ChromPos_: Position(s) on contig(s) with the best alignment of marker / tag to an existing model genome
alncoldetails.AlnCnt_: Total count of aligning markers / tags with selection criteria described below

Report_DY17-1234_SilicoDArT.csv.description: SilicoDArT Format: SilicoDArTs are scored in a binary fashion, representing genetically "dominant" markers, with "1"=Presence and "0"=Absence of a restriction fragment with the marker sequence in genomic representation of the sample. "-" represents calls with non-zero counts, but too low counts to score confidently as "1" (often representing heterozygotes)

metacolsdetails.SNP: In 2 rows format: this column is blank in the Reference row, and contains the base position and base variant details in the SNP row. In 1 row format: contains the base position and base variant details
metacolsdetails.FreqHomSnp: The proportion of samples which score as homozygous for the SNP allele
metacolsdetails.CallRate: The proportion of samples for which the genotype call is either "1" or "0", rather than "-"
metacolsdetails.AlleleSequence: In 1 row format: the sequence of the Reference allele. In 2 rows format: the sequence of the Reference allele is in the Ref row, the sequence of the SNP allele in the SNP row
metacolsdetails.TrimmedSequence: Same as the full sequence, but with removed adapters in short marker tags
metacolsdetails.OneRatioRef: The proportion of samples for which the genotype score is "1", in the Reference allele row
metacolsdetails.AvgCountRef: The sum of the tag read counts for all samples, divided by the number of samples with non-zero tag read counts, for the Reference allele row
metacolsdetails.FreqHets: The proportion of samples which score as heterozygous.
metacolsdetails.AvgCountSnp: The sum of the tag read counts for all samples, divided by the number of samples with non-zero tag read counts, for the SNP allele row
metacolsdetails.AlleleID: Unique identifier for the sequence in which the SNP marker occurs
metacolsdetails.AvgPIC: The average of the polymorphism information content (PIC) of the Reference and SNP allele rows
metacolsdetails.RepAvg: The proportion of technical replicate assay pairs for which the marker score is consistent
metacolsdetails.FreqHomRef: The proportion of samples which score as homozygous for the Reference allele
metacolsdetails.PICSnp: The polymorphism information content (PIC) for the SNP allele row
metacolsdetails.PICRef: The polymorphism information content (PIC) for the Reference allele row
metacolsdetails.SnpPosition: The position (zero indexed) in the sequence tag at which the defined SNP variant base occurs
metacolsdetails.OneRatioSnp: The proportion of samples for which the genotype score is "1", in the SNP allele row
